.[1][4] The poet was a disciple of Swami Manavala Mamuni, who composed Sri Ranganatha Suprabhatam. Sri Venkatesa Suprabhatam consists of four parts: Suprabhatam, Sri Venkatesa Stothram, Prapatti, and Mangalasasanam. Lakshmi Narayana deity, Sri-Bhu Devi sametha Padmanabha Swamy deity and 12 divya salagrama silas once worshiped by him are now with Prativada Bhayankaram Raghavacharyulu 15th generation from Sri Annan Swamy. These are now being worshiped daily at Divya Salagrama Kshetram in Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh. Devanagari            IAST kausalysupraj rma prv sandhy pravartate  uttiha narardla karttavya daivamhnikam             uttihottiha govinda uttiha garuadhvaja  uttiha kamalknta trailokya magala kuru             mtassamastajagat madhukaiabhre vakovihrii manoharadivyamrte  rsvmini ritajanapriyadnale rvekaeadayite tava suprabhtam           tava suprabhtamaravindalocane bhavatu prasannamukhacandramaale  vidhiakarendravanitbhirarcite vaailanthadayite daynidhe   -           atrydisaptaayassamupsya sandhy- mkasindhukamalni manohari  dya pdayugamarcayitu prapann edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam              pacnanbjabhavaamukhavsavdy traivikramdicarita vibudh stuvanti  bhpati pahati vsarauddhimrt edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam  -           atpraphullasarasruhanrikela- pgadrumdisumanoharapliknm  vti mandamanila saha divyagandhai edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam              unmlya netrayugamuttamapajarasth ptrvaiakadalphalapyasni  bhuktv sallamatha keliuk pahanti edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam             tantrprakaramadhurasvanay vipacy gyatyanantacarita tava nrado'pi  bhsamagramasaktkaracruramya edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam              bhgval ca makarandarasnuviddh jhakragtaninadai saha sevanya  nirytyupntasaraskamalodarebhya edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam               yogaena varadadhnivimathyamne golayeu dadhimanthanatvragho  rotkali vidadhate kakubhca kumbh edriekharavibho tava suprabhtam               padmeamitraatapatragatlivarg hartu riya kuvalayasya ni